com.northconcepts.datapipeline.core

Class Record

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.northconcepts.datapipeline.core.Node
      • com.northconcepts.datapipeline.core.ValueNode<Record>
        • com.northconcepts.datapipeline.core.Record
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Session, Serializable, Cloneable, Comparable<ValueNode<Record>>, Iterable<Field>

    public final class Record
extends ValueNode<Record>
implements Cloneable, Serializable, Iterable<Field>
    Record holds persistent data in key-value fields as it flows through the pipeline. Values in a field can be:
    • Single values (boolean, date, string, etc. -- see FieldType)
    • Records
    • Array of single values, records, and arrays
      See Also:
      SingleValue, ArrayValue, Field, FieldType, Serialized Form

          public Field getField(FieldList fieldNamePath,
                      boolean createField)
          Retrieves a nested child field. If createField is true, all missing intermediate records will be created, otherwise an exception will be thrown. This method will fail if an intermediate field has a non-record, non-null value.

        • addField

          public Field addField(String fieldName,
                      Object value,
                      boolean arrayField)
          Adds a new field with the specified value to this record. If a field with this name already exists, arrayField determines if the existing field should be promoted to an array and the new value added to it, otherwise, a unique name is created for the new value by appending a number to the name starting with 1 until an unused name is found.

        • addField

          public Field addField(String fieldName,
                      Object value)
          Adds a new field with the specified value to this record. If a field with this name already exists, this method searches for an unused name by appending an numeric offset starting with 1.
